        Portuguese). If necessary, locale-specific customizations can be provided by adding a region designator to the
        file name (for example, <filepath class="+ topic/ph sw-d/filepath " xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/pdf-plugin-structure.dita" xtrc="filepath:22;65:43">pt_BR.xml</filepath> for Brazilian Portuguese).</p>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/pdf-plugin-structure.dita" xtrc="p:15;66:10">The index files consist of <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/pdf-plugin-structure.dita" xtrc="xmlelement:5;66:49">index.group</xmlelement> elements which contain sorting information on
        one or more characters. Index groups are listed in sort order (“specials” before numbers, numbers before the
        letter ‘A‘, etc), and the <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/pdf-plugin-structure.dita" xtrc="xmlelement:6;68:47">char.set</xmlelement> entries they contain are also listed in sort order
