        the published outputs. For example, page headers, hyperlinks, etc. The id attribute for each variable should
        make it clear how the variable text is being used.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/pdf-plugin-structure.dita" xtrc="p:20;85:10">Some variables contain <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrf="file:/Users/ekimber/workspace-ditaot/dita-ot-2.x/src/main/docsrc/dev_ref/pdf-plugin-structure.dita" xtrc="xmlelement:8;85:45">param</xmlelement> elements which indicate parameter values that are
        substituted at publish time by the XSL. For example, a page number that is being generated as part of the
